Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.78,0:07:35.04,1080CN UP,,0,0,0,,百度百科上说是2016年7月31日停止工作的
Dialogue: 1,0:00:00.52,0:00:05.74,1080CN,,0,0,0,,这张图展示了最近的一份近地轨道太空垃圾调查
Dialogue: 2,0:00:00.52,0:00:05.74,1080EN,,0,0,0,,This chart shows a recent survey of satellites and space junk in low-earth orbits
Dialogue: 1,0:00:05.93,0:00:08.65,1080CN,,0,0,0,,左边竖列是制造垃圾的国家
Dialogue: 2,0:00:05.93,0:00:08.65,1080EN,,0,0,0,,listed by of a country responsible for creating it
Dialogue: 1,0:00:08.99,0:00:15.08,1080CN,,0,0,0,,第三名你可能没想到，中国竟然和俄罗斯、美国有一样多的太空垃圾
Dialogue: 2,0:00:08.99,0:00:15.08,1080EN,,0,0,0,,The third country might be a surprise to you, China has left almost as much debris as America and Russia
Dialogue: 1,0:00:15.42,0:00:17.95,1080CN,,0,0,0,,虽然他们的太空史没那么悠久
Dialogue: 2,0:00:15.42,0:00:17.95,1080EN,,0,0,0,,despite having a much shorter history in space
Dialogue: 1,0:00:18.46,0:00:22.59,1080CN,,0,0,0,,实际上这当中大多数来自于2007年的一次导弹试验
Dialogue: 2,0:00:18.46,0:00:22.59,1080EN,,0,0,0,,In fact most of this was from just one missile test in 2007
Dialogue: 1,0:00:22.80,0:00:27.93,1080CN,,0,0,0,,当时中国发射了一发动能弹头击毁了一颗已退役的卫星
Dialogue: 2,0:00:22.80,0:00:27.93,1080EN,,0,0,0,,when China fired a kinetic kill vehicle that one of its own retired weather satellites
Dialogue: 1,0:00:28.46,0:00:32.48,1080CN,,0,0,0,,击中时相对速度有每秒8千米
Dialogue: 2,0:00:28.46,0:00:32.48,1080EN,,0,0,0,,The missile hit at a relative speed of about 8 km/s
Dialogue: 1,0:00:32.73,0:00:38.54,1080CN,,0,0,0,,把卫星炸成900个大碎片和35,000个小碎片
Dialogue: 2,0:00:32.73,0:00:38.54,1080EN,,0,0,0,,shattering the satellite into more than 900 large pieces and almost 35,000 small objects
Dialogue: 1,0:00:38.92,0:00:42.54,1080CN,,0,0,0,,它们中绝大多数都会在轨道停留几十甚至上百年
Dialogue: 2,0:00:38.92,0:00:42.54,1080EN,,0,0,0,,many of these will remain in orbit for decades or even centuries
Dialogue: 1,0:00:43.00,0:00:50.17,1080CN,,0,0,0,,上次提起此事我当时还评论谴责了下中国的做法
Dialogue: 2,0:00:43.00,0:00:50.17,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Now the last time I mentioned China's 2007 missile test I got some flak in the comments for picking on China
Dialogue: 1,0:00:50.27,0:00:54.40,1080CN,,0,0,0,,但也没办法，这事其他好多国家也都干过
Dialogue: 2,0:00:50.27,0:00:54.40,1080EN,,0,0,0,,so yes other nations also have done similar things
Dialogue: 1,0:00:54.68,0:00:59.92,1080CN,,0,0,0,,产生的这些太空垃圾也是太空军备计划的典型产物
Dialogue: 2,0:00:54.68,0:00:59.92,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and its legacy of space junk is typical of early missions in many national space programs
Dialogue: 1,0:01:00.24,0:01:06.62,1080CN,,0,0,0,,上世纪五十年代国际普遍认为近地空间将是一个新的战场
Dialogue: 2,0:01:00.24,0:01:06.62,1080EN,,0,0,0,,In the 1950's global powers faced the likelihood that Low Earth Orbit would become the new battleground overhead
Dialogue: 1,0:01:06.89,0:01:10.19,1080CN,,0,0,0,,谁掌握了那里谁就能在未来战争中手握王牌
Dialogue: 2,0:01:06.89,0:01:10.19,1080EN,,0,0,0,,and control of that space will be a deciding factor in future wars
Dialogue: 1,0:01:10.49,0:01:16.03,1080CN,,0,0,115,,在1958年，中华人民共和国主席毛泽东同志决定发展太空计划
Dialogue: 2,0:01:10.49,0:01:16.03,1080EN,,0,0,80,,In 1958 Chairman Mao Zedong announced a plan to develop a space launch capability
Dialogue: 1,0:01:16.20,0:01:18.72,1080CN,,0,0,0,,从建造洲际导弹计划开始
Dialogue: 2,0:01:16.20,0:01:18.72,1080EN,,0,0,0,,from a country's ballistic missile program
Dialogue: 1,0:01:19.08,0:01:24.20,1080CN,,0,0,0,,然而中国和苏联关系在五十年代到六十年代早期逐渐恶化
Dialogue: 2,0:01:19.08,0:01:24.20,1080EN,,0,0,0,,However when relations between the Soviet Union and China cooled in the late 1950s and early 60s
Dialogue: 1,0:01:24.64,0:01:27.29,1080CN,,0,0,0,,苏联的技术团队也全都撤回
Dialogue: 2,0:01:24.64,0:01:27.29,1080EN,,0,0,0,,The Russian technical assistance also went away
Dialogue: 1,0:01:27.79,0:01:31.36,1080CN,,0,0,0,,也尽管中国在六七十年代经济发展缓慢
Dialogue: 2,0:01:27.79,0:01:31.36,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Although the Chinese economy grew slowly in the 60s and 70s
Dialogue: 1,0:01:31.64,0:01:37.39,1080CN,,0,0,115,,但中国的确成为了世界上第五个独立研制并发射卫星的国家
Dialogue: 2,0:01:31.64,0:01:37.39,1080EN,,0,0,80,,they did become the fifth nation to independently develop and launch their own satellite system
Dialogue: 1,0:01:37.53,0:01:41.00,1080CN,,0,0,115,,1970年4月，长征一号发射成功
Dialogue: 2,0:01:37.53,0:01:41.00,1080EN,,0,0,80,,with the long march one rocket in April 1970
Dialogue: 1,0:01:41.56,0:01:45.76,1080CN,,0,0,165,,接下来二十年中国的载人航天计划一直在搁置
Dialogue: 2,0:01:41.56,0:01:45.76,1080EN,,0,0,130,,Over the next two decades plans for manned space flight were put on hold
Dialogue: 1,0:01:46.09,0:01:50.39,1080CN,,0,0,0,,太空发射主要还是中国的卫星
Dialogue: 2,0:01:46.09,0:01:50.39,1080EN,,0,0,0,,but the space launches continued to deploy mostly Chinese satellites
Dialogue: 1,0:01:50.70,0:01:59.66,1080CN,,0,0,0,,实际上如今中国已经使用长征系列火箭发射258次，成功率94.6%
Dialogue: 2,0:01:50.70,0:01:59.66,1080EN,,0,0,0,,In fact today there have been 258 launches using the Long March family of rockets with a success rate of 94.6%
Dialogue: 1,0:02:00.09,0:02:06.90,1080CN,,0,0,115,,直到1992年，现代化的中国的领导者才再次看到太空计划的价值
Dialogue: 2,0:02:00.09,0:02:06.90,1080EN,,0,0,80,,It took until 1992 before the leadership of a modernized China saw value in a space program again
Dialogue: 1,0:02:07.18,0:02:10.89,1080CN,,0,0,0,,——刺激、促进工程、科学领域的高端技术发展
Dialogue: 2,0:02:07.18,0:02:10.89,1080EN,,0,0,0,,as a way to stimulate and demonstrate advances in engineering and science
Dialogue: 1,0:02:11.32,0:02:19.05,1080CN,,0,0,115,,1992年，921工程被提出，中国决定送人上太空
Dialogue: 2,0:02:11.32,0:02:19.05,1080EN,,0,0,80,,In 1992 project 921 was approved its objective to establish a manned Chinese presence in space
Dialogue: 1,0:02:19.24,0:02:23.23,1080CN,,0,0,0,,921的第一步是造能载人的飞船
Dialogue: 2,0:02:19.24,0:02:23.23,1080EN,,0,0,0,,The first step of a new program was to develop a human rated capsule
Dialogue: 1,0:02:23.72,0:02:30.36,1080CN,,0,0,0,,“神舟”号飞船在1999年11月进行了一次成功的无人试飞
Dialogue: 2,0:02:23.72,0:02:30.36,1080EN,,0,0,0,,'Shenzhou' meaning divine vessel flew a successful unmanned test flight in November 1999
Dialogue: 1,0:02:30.70,0:02:35.87,1080CN,,0,0,0,,两年后，神舟二号携带几只动物测试了生命保障系统
Dialogue: 2,0:02:30.70,0:02:35.87,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Two years later 'Shenzhou 2' - carried animals on board to test the life-support systems
Dialogue: 1,0:02:36.14,0:02:38.88,1080CN,,0,0,115,,包括猴子、狗、兔子、几只蜗牛
Dialogue: 2,0:02:36.14,0:02:38.88,1080EN,,0,0,80,,a monkey a dog a rabbit and some snails
Dialogue: 1,0:02:39.48,0:02:45.63,1080CN,,0,0,0,,尽管研发之路很曲折，但神舟五号还是在2003年10月15日上天了
Dialogue: 2,0:02:39.48,0:02:45.63,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Despite setbacks progress on Shenzhou developed steadily and on October 15th 2003
Dialogue: 1,0:02:45.90,0:02:50.81,1080CN,,0,0,0,,杨利伟，中国第一位进入太空的航天员
Dialogue: 2,0:02:45.90,0:02:50.81,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Yang Liwei, the first Taikonaut traveled on board Shenzhou 5
Dialogue: 1,0:02:51.00,0:02:55.76,1080CN,,0,0,0,,使中国成为第三个独立送人进太空的国家
Dialogue: 2,0:02:51.00,0:02:55.76,1080EN,,0,0,0,,making China the third nation to independently carry a human into space
Dialogue: 1,0:02:56.24,0:03:02.49,1080CN,,0,0,0,,汉语里的“太空”加上英语的naut，合起来就是Taikonaut
Dialogue: 2,0:02:56.24,0:03:02.49,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Now the Mandarin word for space is 'taikong' add the Western word naut and you have Taikonaut
Dialogue: 1,0:03:02.73,0:03:04.03,1080CN,,0,0,0,,中国版的“航天员”
Dialogue: 2,0:03:02.73,0:03:04.03,1080EN,,0,0,0,,the Chinese version of astronaut
Dialogue: 1,0:03:04.52,0:03:09.53,1080CN,,0,0,115,,杨利伟在太空呆了21小时，绕地球14圈
Dialogue: 2,0:03:04.52,0:03:09.53,1080EN,,0,0,80,,Liwei completed 14 orbits of the earth in a little over 21 hours
Dialogue: 1,0:03:09.61,0:03:16.01,1080CN,,0,0,0,,其间在相机前挥舞了中华人民共和国国旗与联合国国旗庆祝
Dialogue: 2,0:03:09.61,0:03:16.01,1080EN,,0,0,0,,celebrating by waving the flags of the People's Republic of China and the United Nations to the onboard cameras
Dialogue: 1,0:03:16.48,0:03:21.18,1080CN,,0,0,0,,921工程下一步是造一个小型空间站
Dialogue: 2,0:03:16.48,0:03:21.18,1080EN,,0,0,0,,The next phase of project 921 was to establish a small space station
Dialogue: 1,0:03:21.56,0:03:30.86,1080CN,,0,0,115,,2011年中国造了8.5吨的天宫一号
Dialogue: 2,0:03:21.56,0:03:30.86,1080EN,,0,0,80,,By 2011 for Chinese space agency had constructed and prepared the eight and a half ton tiangong 1 or 'Heavenly Palace'
Dialogue: 1,0:03:31.44,0:03:36.67,1080CN,,0,0,0,,允许三位航天员驻留几周的太空实验室
Dialogue: 2,0:03:31.44,0:03:36.67,1080EN,,0,0,0,,the Space Lab was capable of supporting three Taikonaut's for scientific missions up to a few weeks
Dialogue: 1,0:03:37.05,0:03:40.73,1080CN,,0,0,0,,内部涂有两种颜色，分别代表天和地
Dialogue: 2,0:03:37.05,0:03:40.73,1080EN,,0,0,0,,The interior was painted in two colors to represent the sky and the ground
Dialogue: 1,0:03:40.96,0:03:44.24,1080CN,,0,0,0,,帮助航天员在微重力环境下区分上下
Dialogue: 2,0:03:40.96,0:03:44.24,1080EN,,0,0,0,,helping the Taikonauts to orientate themselves in micro-gravity
Dialogue: 1,0:03:44.64,0:03:51.40,1080CN,,0,0,0,,天宫一号的主要目标是验证与神舟飞船的对接
Dialogue: 2,0:03:44.64,0:03:51.40,1080EN,,0,0,0,,However the main purpose of a prototype was as a target vehicle to test docking with the Shenzhou capsule
Dialogue: 1,0:03:52.16,0:03:58.51,1080CN,,0,0,0,,但当天宫一号完成了其最后一项地面测试后，中国航天出事了
Dialogue: 2,0:03:52.16,0:03:58.51,1080EN,,0,0,0,,but while the Tiangong-1 was completing its final ground tests the Chinese space agency faced a new problem
Dialogue: 1,0:03:59.04,0:04:06.68,1080CN,,0,0,0,,8月18日，长征二号丙火箭因二级发动机工作故障而发射失败
Dialogue: 2,0:03:59.04,0:04:06.68,1080EN,,0,0,0,,On August the 18th a Long March 2C rocket suffered a failure during the second stage engine burn and it was lost
Dialogue: 1,0:04:07.08,0:04:11.29,1080CN,,0,0,0,,如果相同的事情发生在天宫一号的发射、或者载人任务的发射上
Dialogue: 2,0:04:07.08,0:04:11.29,1080EN,,0,0,0,,If the same thing happened during the launch of a Tiangong-1 or a manned mission
Dialogue: 1,0:04:11.50,0:04:14.38,1080CN,,0,0,0,,那就GG了
Dialogue: 2,0:04:11.50,0:04:14.38,1080EN,,0,0,0,,it would be disastrous for the entire space program
Dialogue: 1,0:04:14.68,0:04:20.97,1080CN,,0,0,0,,工程师们在六个月内赶紧对长征二号进行了170多种改进
Dialogue: 2,0:04:14.68,0:04:20.97,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Engineers hurriedly made more than a 170 modifications to the Long March 2 in just six weeks
Dialogue: 1,0:04:21.28,0:04:27.00,1080CN,,0,0,0,,研发出的F-T1型终于能够发射中国的第一个空间实验室了
Dialogue: 2,0:04:21.28,0:04:27.00,1080EN,,0,0,0,,resulting in the new "FT-1" version which was approved to carry China's first Space Lab
Dialogue: 1,0:04:27.45,0:04:34.00,1080CN,,0,0,0,,2011年9月28日，天宫一号发射成功
Dialogue: 2,0:04:27.45,0:04:34.00,1080EN,,0,0,0,,On September 29th 2011 Heavenly Palace successfully launched into its target orbit
Dialogue: 1,0:04:34.33,0:04:42.11,1080CN,,0,0,135,,2012年6月，第一批三位航天员进驻，包括中国第一位女航天员刘洋
Dialogue: 2,0:04:34.33,0:04:42.11,1080EN,,0,0,100,,In June 2012 the first crew of three Taikonauts arrived including China's first woman in space Lu Yang
Dialogue: 1,0:04:42.48,0:04:47.77,1080CN,,0,0,0,,神舟九号成功与天宫一号对接，并驻留11天
Dialogue: 2,0:04:42.48,0:04:47.77,1080EN,,0,0,0,,The Shenzhou 9 spacecraft docked successfully and remained at Tiangong-1 for 11 days
Dialogue: 1,0:04:48.25,0:04:56.41,1080CN,,0,0,0,,在2013年第二批航天员返回后，天宫一号进入待机状态，轨道慢慢降低
Dialogue: 2,0:04:48.25,0:04:56.41,1080EN,,0,0,0,,After another man visit in 2013 Tiangong-1 was put into sleep mode and its orbit has been gradually decaying ever since
Dialogue: 1,0:04:56.97,0:05:07.88,1080CN UP,,0,0,0,,视频在YouTube发布的时候 天宫一号还没掉下来
Dialogue: 1,0:04:56.97,0:05:01.50,1080CN,,0,0,0,,现在它也差不多该落回地球了
Dialogue: 2,0:04:56.97,0:05:01.50,1080EN,,0,0,0,,But it's almost time for the first 'Heavenly Palace' to come back down to earth
Dialogue: 1,0:05:02.09,0:05:07.82,1080CN,,0,0,0,,2018年早期全世界几个航天机构都会追踪它
Dialogue: 2,0:05:02.09,0:05:07.82,1080EN,,0,0,0,,In the early months of 2018 the inter-agency space debris Coordination Committee will track
Dialogue: 1,0:05:08.16,0:05:13.18,1080CN,,0,0,0,,并且逐渐缩小再入大气时间的预测范围
Dialogue: 2,0:05:08.16,0:05:13.18,1080EN,,0,0,0,,the space labs reentry to further refine its prediction of where it might end up
Dialogue: 1,0:05:13.71,0:05:17.71,1080CN,,0,0,0,,2016年9月，第二个空间实验室，天宫二号
Dialogue: 1,0:05:13.53,0:05:15.08,1080CN UP,,0,0,0,,提问 箭体上的“神箭”是谁写的？
Dialogue: 2,0:05:13.71,0:05:17.71,1080EN,,0,0,0,,In September 2016 a second orbital lab Tiangong-2
Dialogue: 1,0:05:17.71,0:05:22.75,1080CN,,0,0,0,,在酒泉卫星发射中心发射，几个月后与载两人的神舟十一号对接
Dialogue: 2,0:05:17.71,0:05:22.75,1080EN,,0,0,0,,launched from the Jiuquan Launch Center in the Gobi Desert to be joined a month later by
Dialogue: 1,0:05:22.75,0:05:25.18,1080CN,,0,0,0,,在酒泉卫星发射中心发射，几个月后与载两人的神舟十一号对接
Dialogue: 2,0:05:22.75,0:05:25.18,1080EN,,0,0,0,,two-man crew aboard at Shenzhou 11
Dialogue: 1,0:05:25.61,0:05:28.72,1080CN,,0,0,0,,天宫二号设计与大小和天宫一号很接近
Dialogue: 2,0:05:25.61,0:05:28.72,1080EN,,0,0,0,,With a similar size and design to the first Heavenly Palace
Dialogue: 1,0:05:28.94,0:05:34.96,1080CN,,0,0,0,,让航天员景海鹏与陈冬在上面停留了30天
Dialogue: 2,0:05:28.94,0:05:34.96,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Tiangong-2 - was able to support Taikonauts Jing Haipeng and Chen Dong for 30 days
Dialogue: 1,0:05:35.77,0:05:38.80,1080CN,,0,0,0,,其间他们测试了很多科学仪器
Dialogue: 2,0:05:35.77,0:05:38.80,1080EN,,0,0,0,,During this time they tested a range of scientific instruments
Dialogue: 1,0:05:38.80,0:05:42.96,1080CN,,0,0,0,,包括第一个空间冷原子钟
Dialogue: 2,0:05:38.80,0:05:42.96,1080EN,,0,0,0,,including the first ever cold atomic clock experiment in space
Dialogue: 1,0:05:43.20,0:05:46.32,1080CN,,0,0,0,,在比绝对零度高零点几度的温度工作
Dialogue: 2,0:05:43.20,0:05:46.32,1080EN,,0,0,0,,which operated at a fraction of degree above absolute zero
Dialogue: 1,0:05:46.49,0:05:50.78,1080CN,,0,0,0,,每百万年误差一秒
Dialogue: 2,0:05:46.49,0:05:50.78,1080EN,,0,0,0,,so accurate but it only loses one second every billion years
Dialogue: 1,0:05:51.07,0:05:54.33,1080CN,,0,0,0,,中国除了搞载人航天计划
Dialogue: 2,0:05:51.07,0:05:54.33,1080EN,,0,0,0,,As well as setting up an independent manned space program
Dialogue: 1,0:05:54.36,0:05:58.60,1080CN,,0,0,0,,还研究了几个新的高科技月球车
Dialogue: 2,0:05:54.36,0:05:58.60,1080EN,,0,0,0,,China is also breaking new ground with a serious high-tech moon Landers
Dialogue: 1,0:05:59.15,0:06:06.67,1080CN,,0,0,0,,2013年12月1日，1200千克的嫦娥三号着陆器发射前往月球
Dialogue: 2,0:05:59.15,0:06:06.67,1080EN,,0,0,0,,On the 1st of December 2013 a 1200 kilogram Lander named Chang'E 3 launched on a mission to the moon
Dialogue: 1,0:06:06.88,0:06:12.94,1080CN,,0,0,0,,五天后嫦娥三号进入100千米高的近月轨道
Dialogue: 2,0:06:06.88,0:06:12.94,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Five days after a launch Chang'E 3 entered an orbit approaching 100 km altitude above all in the lunar surface
Dialogue: 1,0:06:13.39,0:06:17.04,1080CN,,0,0,0,,在12月4日，第二次减速点火后
Dialogue: 2,0:06:13.39,0:06:17.04,1080EN,,0,0,0,,After a second decelerating burn on the 14th of December
Dialogue: 1,0:06:17.23,0:06:22.14,1080CN,,0,0,0,,着陆器缓缓下降至月球表面雨海的一百米高处
Dialogue: 2,0:06:17.23,0:06:22.14,1080EN,,0,0,0,,the lander descended to just a hundred meters altitude above the Mare Imbrium
Dialogue: 1,0:06:22.43,0:06:27.08,1080CN,,0,0,0,,悬停的同时，相机寻找合适的着陆点
Dialogue: 2,0:06:22.43,0:06:27.08,1080EN,,0,0,0,,hovering in position whilst it's onboard cameras located the clear landing site
Dialogue: 1,0:06:27.61,0:06:30.62,1080CN,,0,0,0,,12分钟着陆程序执行后
Dialogue: 2,0:06:27.61,0:06:30.62,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Executing a 12-minute landing sequence
Dialogue: 1,0:06:30.83,0:06:36.41,1080CN,,0,0,0,,嫦娥三号成功着陆，37年后月球表面又一次有人类的探测器来访
Dialogue: 2,0:06:30.83,0:06:36.41,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Chang'E 3 touchdowned successfully, the first lunar soft landing in 37 years
Dialogue: 1,0:06:36.78,0:06:38.60,1080CN,,0,0,0,,但任务才刚开始
Dialogue: 2,0:06:36.78,0:06:38.60,1080EN,,0,0,0,,But the mission was far from over
Dialogue: 1,0:06:38.76,0:06:42.19,1080CN,,0,0,115,,就像苏联在七十年代的月球车一样
Dialogue: 2,0:06:38.76,0:06:42.19,1080EN,,0,0,80,,Like the soviet Lunokhod rovers of the early 1970s
Dialogue: 1,0:06:42.33,0:06:47.29,1080CN,,0,0,0,,嫦娥三号装有核动力的发热单元，让其熬过月球上的漫漫长夜
Dialogue: 2,0:06:42.33,0:06:47.29,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Chang'E 3 was equipped with a nuclear-powered heating unit to survive the harsh lunar nights
Dialogue: 1,0:06:47.56,0:06:55.32,1080CN,,0,0,0,,除了各种科学仪器，中国的月球着陆器还有一个140千克的玉兔号月球车
Dialogue: 2,0:06:47.56,0:06:55.32,1080EN,,0,0,0,,As well as having an array of scientific instruments, the Chinese Lander also carried a 140 kilogram Rover called Yutu
Dialogue: 1,0:06:55.74,0:06:58.99,1080CN,,0,0,0,,它探索了着陆点附近的火山口
Dialogue: 2,0:06:55.74,0:06:58.99,1080EN,,0,0,0,,which explored the volcanic crater near the landing site
Dialogue: 1,0:06:59.40,0:07:03.20,1080CN,,0,0,0,,玉兔的名字来自中国的古老传说
Dialogue: 2,0:06:59.40,0:07:03.20,1080EN,,0,0,0,,The rover was named by public poll in Chinese mythology
Dialogue: 1,0:07:03.31,0:07:06.41,1080CN,,0,0,115,,玉兔是象征月亮的女神——嫦娥的宠物兔子
Dialogue: 2,0:07:03.31,0:07:06.41,1080EN,,0,0,80,,Yutu was the pet rabbit of Chang'E, the moon goddess
Dialogue: 1,0:07:06.62,0:07:11.50,1080CN,,0,0,115,,所以西方我们叫它“玉做的兔子”、“月亮兔”或者干脆叫“兔子”
Dialogue: 2,0:07:06.62,0:07:11.50,1080EN,,0,0,80,,so in the West we know the rover as the Jade rabbit, moon rabbit or just rabbit
Dialogue: 1,0:07:12.00,0:07:17.34,1080CN,,0,0,0,,但玉兔号在2014年1月发生了一点小故障
Dialogue: 2,0:07:12.00,0:07:17.34,1080EN,,0,0,0,,But this particular rabbit came to a bit of a sticky intermittent end in January 2014
Dialogue: 1,0:07:17.53,0:07:22.78,1080CN,,0,0,0,,据中国国防科工局说是“机构控制出现异常”
Dialogue: 2,0:07:17.53,0:07:22.78,1080EN,,0,0,0,,when it had a "mechanical control abnormality" according to the Chinese state media
Dialogue: 1,0:07:23.16,0:07:28.60,1080CN,,0,0,0,,西方普遍认为原因是月球上的尘土让机械部件出现故障
Dialogue: 2,0:07:23.16,0:07:28.60,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Although many in the West believe it fell victim to be highly unforgiving the lunar dust jamming its mechanics
Dialogue: 1,0:07:29.32,0:07:31.78,1080CN,,0,0,115,,玉兔后来断断续续的和地球有所联系
Dialogue: 2,0:07:29.32,0:07:31.78,1080EN,,0,0,80,,It intermittently communicated back again with earth up
Dialogue: 1,0:07:31.78,0:07:35.04,1080CN,,0,0,115,,直到2015年3月停止工作
Dialogue: 2,0:07:31.78,0:07:35.04,1080EN,,0,0,80,,until March 2015 when it finally fell silent
Dialogue: 1,0:07:35.32,0:07:42.62,1080CN,,0,0,0,,但中国说没玩够，2018年嫦娥三号的备份嫦娥四号要在月球背面着陆
Dialogue: 2,0:07:35.32,0:07:42.62,1080EN,,0,0,0,,But China aims to go even further in 2018 when the backup lander of a Chang 3 mission is scheduled to do a touchdown
Dialogue: 1,0:07:42.62,0:07:45.84,1080CN,,0,0,0,,但中国说没玩够，2018年嫦娥三号的备份嫦娥四号要在月球背面着陆
Dialogue: 2,0:07:42.62,0:07:45.84,1080EN,,0,0,0,,on the far side of a moon as Chang'E 4
Dialogue: 1,0:07:46.14,0:07:47.82,1080CN,,0,0,0,,这可是很厉害的第一次
Dialogue: 2,0:07:46.14,0:07:47.82,1080EN,,0,0,0,,This will be an impressive first
Dialogue: 1,0:07:48.11,0:07:53.98,1080CN,,0,0,0,,因为之前美国和苏联的所有软着陆都在月球面向地球那侧
Dialogue: 2,0:07:48.11,0:07:53.98,1080EN,,0,0,0,,All the American and Soviet soft landings were executed in direct line of sight with the earth
Dialogue: 1,0:07:54.44,0:07:58.01,1080CN,,0,0,115,,计划着陆点在南极-艾托肯盆地
Dialogue: 2,0:07:54.44,0:07:58.01,1080EN,,0,0,80,,The proposed landing site is the 'South Pole-Aitken basin'
Dialogue: 1,0:07:58.08,0:08:04.28,1080CN,,0,0,115,,太阳系中已知的最大陨石坑，直径2500千米
Dialogue: 2,0:07:58.08,0:08:04.28,1080EN,,0,0,80,,a candidate for the largest impact crater in the solar system with a diameter of 2500 km
Dialogue: 1,0:08:04.89,0:08:10.12,1080CN,,0,0,0,,在那里，中国的着陆器可以研究月球暴露出的15千米的地壳
Dialogue: 2,0:08:04.89,0:08:10.12,1080EN,,0,0,0,,Here the Chinese Lander will be able to examine 15 kilometers of exposed crust
Dialogue: 1,0:08:10.44,0:08:15.07,1080CN,,0,0,0,,希望能找到些证据帮助我们了解月球那千疮百孔的过去
Dialogue: 2,0:08:10.44,0:08:15.07,1080EN,,0,0,0,,hopefully uncovering evidence to help us understand the moon's violent past better
Dialogue: 1,0:08:15.32,0:08:21.47,1080CN,,0,0,0,,2016年中国发射了22发火箭，比俄罗斯多，和美国一样多
Dialogue: 2,0:08:15.32,0:08:21.47,1080EN,,0,0,0,,In 2016 China launched 22 rockets that's more than the Russians and the same number as the US
Dialogue: 1,0:08:21.88,0:08:27.53,1080CN,,0,0,0,,中国在本世纪二十年代计划发射第三个空间站和一个太空望远镜
Dialogue: 2,0:08:21.88,0:08:27.53,1080EN,,0,0,0,,it has plans for a third space station and its own space telescope in the mid-2020s
Dialogue: 1,0:08:27.66,0:08:31.36,1080CN,,0,0,0,,并在三十年代中期登月
Dialogue: 2,0:08:27.66,0:08:31.36,1080EN,,0,0,0,,with aims to put men on the moon by the mid 2030s
Dialogue: 1,0:08:31.69,0:08:37.77,1080CN,,0,0,0,,目前看来NASA、ESA和太空叉在不久的将来会多一个不好对付的竞争对手
Dialogue: 2,0:08:31.69,0:08:37.77,1080EN,,0,0,0,,so it looks like NASA, ESA and SpaceX will have some serious competition in the near future
